1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,459
[WOMAN] Welcome to Siargao, Sir…?

2
00:00:01,501 --> 00:00:02,377
[JAO] Jao.

3
00:00:02,377 --> 00:00:04,879
Jao? As in “very good”?

4
00:00:04,879 --> 00:00:06,297
[WOMAN] Is it your first time in Siargao?

5
00:00:06,297 --> 00:00:07,841
Are you lost? You need help?

6
00:00:07,882 --> 00:00:08,800
Do you know this person?

7
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:10,051
Do you know her?

8
00:00:10,051 --> 00:00:11,469
Waves good?

9
00:00:11,553 --> 00:00:12,804
I’m proud of you!

10
00:00:12,804 --> 00:00:14,055
You’re not so reckless anymore.

11
00:00:14,055 --> 00:00:14,889
Not anymore?

12
00:00:14,931 --> 00:00:16,599
Was I impulsive?

13
00:00:16,599 --> 00:00:17,934
Anyone would be lucky

14
00:00:17,976 --> 00:00:19,102
to be loved by you.

15
00:00:19,102 --> 00:00:19,894
[HAN BIN] Hello!

16
00:00:19,936 --> 00:00:21,479
[SIARGAONON] Good morning!

17
00:00:21,521 --> 00:00:22,731
My name is Han Bin.

18
00:00:22,772 --> 00:00:24,149
I co-own this resort.

19
00:00:24,149 --> 00:00:26,151
Hi, I’m Jao. Nice to meet you.

20
00:00:26,192 --> 00:00:28,695
So, is this your first time in Siargao?

21
00:00:28,695 --> 00:00:29,696
What is this for?

22
00:00:29,696 --> 00:00:31,698
Maybe you can give it to…?

23
00:00:31,740 --> 00:00:33,616
Stop teasing me! I’m your boss.

24
00:00:33,616 --> 00:00:35,493
We’re the face of Siargao, Pearl.

25
00:00:35,535 --> 00:00:37,454
I know how much you love Siargao, okay?

26
00:00:37,495 --> 00:00:40,039
Because it embraced me as though I’m from here.

27
00:00:40,749 --> 00:00:42,250
I cancelled my flight and

28
00:00:42,292 --> 00:00:44,753
- I’m staying indefinitely. - Way to go!

29
00:00:44,753 --> 00:00:46,755
“The curse is real!”

30
00:00:47,380 --> 00:00:48,465
[PATTY] Can I ask you something?

31
00:00:48,465 --> 00:00:50,008
Are you running away from something?

32
00:00:50,049 --> 00:00:50,800
[KARA] No.

33
00:01:01,936 --> 00:01:02,854
Hi.

34
00:01:03,688 --> 00:01:04,689
Hello?

35
00:01:09,944 --> 00:01:11,613
Allie, my girlfriend.

36
00:01:12,030 --> 00:01:13,198
Do you know her?

37
00:01:13,948 --> 00:01:14,824
Look closely.

38
00:01:14,824 --> 00:01:16,409
- You might know her. - Back off!

39
00:01:16,785 --> 00:01:18,369
Wait up!

40
00:01:18,870 --> 00:01:19,996
Hey, miss!

41
00:01:20,038 --> 00:01:22,165
I was just asking if you know her!

42
00:01:22,248 --> 00:01:23,458
I don’t!

43
00:01:23,625 --> 00:01:25,043
Go home, you’re drunk!

44
00:01:25,794 --> 00:01:26,961
No, I’m not drunk!

45
00:01:27,003 --> 00:01:28,588
Drunk people are like cheaters.

46
00:01:28,588 --> 00:01:30,507
They deny it even when it’s obvious.

47
00:01:31,299 --> 00:01:31,966
Wait, wait, wait.

48
00:01:32,383 --> 00:01:34,010
Are you calling me a cheater?

49
00:01:34,177 --> 00:01:35,136
Or a drunk?

50
00:01:35,136 --> 00:01:37,013
Two things can be true at the same time.

51
00:01:37,555 --> 00:01:38,223
Wow.

52
00:01:38,389 --> 00:01:40,225
You don't even know me. We just met!

53
00:01:40,975 --> 00:01:43,770
I was just asking if you know my girlfriend!

54
00:01:43,770 --> 00:01:44,813
You’re drunk!

55
00:01:44,854 --> 00:01:45,605
Can you go home?

56
00:01:45,647 --> 00:01:46,856
You’re ruining the vibe!

57
00:01:47,190 --> 00:01:47,941
Miss?

58
00:01:49,692 --> 00:01:50,527
Miss!

59
00:01:52,904 --> 00:01:57,242
[ALON BY JL]

60
00:03:12,275 --> 00:03:13,026
Allie?

61
00:03:14,277 --> 00:03:15,278
Sorry.

62
00:03:16,946 --> 00:03:17,947
Sorry!

63
00:03:18,823 --> 00:03:20,533
Hi, love!

64
00:03:20,617 --> 00:03:22,285
Cigarettes!

65
00:03:23,077 --> 00:03:24,078
Hi.

66
00:03:25,121 --> 00:03:26,915
Sorry, I don’t…

67
00:03:27,165 --> 00:03:28,833
I don’t smoke.

68
00:03:30,293 --> 00:03:31,878
But I want to ask

69
00:03:32,211 --> 00:03:33,338
if you know her?

70
00:03:33,379 --> 00:03:34,631
- My girlfriend. - No, sir.

71
00:03:34,672 --> 00:03:35,590
Haven’t seen her around?

72
00:03:35,632 --> 00:03:36,466
No.

73
00:03:37,175 --> 00:03:38,176
Okay.

74
00:03:38,426 --> 00:03:41,971
Can you just tell me…

75
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:45,016
how to get to the after party?

76
00:03:45,266 --> 00:03:46,434
Take that one.

77
00:03:46,434 --> 00:03:48,102
- This? - Yes.

78
00:03:48,102 --> 00:03:49,520
Thanks.

79
00:03:54,275 --> 00:03:55,276
Boss.

80
00:03:55,693 --> 00:03:57,111
What happened, Sir Handsome?

81
00:03:57,153 --> 00:03:58,196
Are you okay?

82
00:03:58,446 --> 00:03:59,948
Can you…

83
00:03:59,948 --> 00:04:02,992
take me to the after party?

84
00:04:03,034 --> 00:04:05,620
I’m looking for my girlfriend. She might be there.

85
00:04:05,620 --> 00:04:07,080
You’re really drunk, Sir Handsome.

86
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:08,498
Where are you staying? I'll take you there.

87
00:04:08,790 --> 00:04:10,166
I'm not-

88
00:04:10,667 --> 00:04:11,834
I’ll take you there, sir.

89
00:04:11,834 --> 00:04:13,503
What’s with people today?

90
00:04:13,544 --> 00:04:15,296
They’ve been acting as if they know me.

91
00:04:15,296 --> 00:04:16,965
- You’re drunk, sir. - I’m not.

92
00:04:17,173 --> 00:04:18,216
I’ll give you a ride.

93
00:04:19,092 --> 00:04:20,426
No, let’s go to the after party.

94
00:04:20,468 --> 00:04:22,804
- I’m looking for Allie. - How many fingers?

95
00:04:24,055 --> 00:04:25,348
[JAO LAUGHS]

96
00:04:25,765 --> 00:04:30,019
Oh, come on…

97
00:04:30,019 --> 00:04:30,812
how many fingers?

98
00:04:30,812 --> 00:04:32,230
How many?

99
00:04:33,439 --> 00:04:35,483
- See, you’re drunk. - Five! Five fingers.

100
00:04:35,525 --> 00:04:36,943
You’re right, but you’re still drunk!

101
00:04:36,943 --> 00:04:38,945
-I’ll give you a ride. Come on. -To the after party?

102
00:04:39,278 --> 00:04:41,030
Let’s go. To the after party.

103
00:04:41,531 --> 00:04:42,782
Come here.

104
00:04:42,782 --> 00:04:43,992
- Allie’s there. - Here you go.

105
00:04:44,033 --> 00:04:46,452
- She might be. - Careful.

106
00:04:46,494 --> 00:04:47,704
She's there!

107
00:04:50,415 --> 00:04:51,958
What a lightweight!

108
00:04:52,208 --> 00:04:54,210
You’re really drunk, Sir Handsome.

109
00:04:54,502 --> 00:04:56,045
You must be hungry.

110
00:04:56,212 --> 00:04:57,422
Let’s go.

111
00:05:09,392 --> 00:05:11,602
[TANTAN] We’re here.

112
00:05:15,273 --> 00:05:16,983
[TANTAN] Are you okay?

113
00:05:17,358 --> 00:05:18,985
I’m fine.

114
00:05:21,029 --> 00:05:23,031
Good evening.

115
00:05:24,198 --> 00:05:27,410
I’ll have…

116
00:05:27,452 --> 00:05:30,288
Three orders of the...

117
00:05:30,329 --> 00:05:32,498
the buy one get one cheeseburger,

118
00:05:32,498 --> 00:05:36,711
then one more order of the buy one get one hotdog

119
00:05:37,003 --> 00:05:40,882
with extra cheese and-

120
00:05:40,923 --> 00:05:42,091
What else is good?

121
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:44,469
Extra cheese and an extra egg!

122
00:05:44,969 --> 00:05:49,682
Plus two bottles of water.

123
00:05:50,141 --> 00:05:51,684
That’s all for me.

124
00:05:52,018 --> 00:05:54,520
What about you? My treat.

125
00:05:54,896 --> 00:05:56,230
You’re so drunk.

126
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:58,566
Just a burger, please.

127
00:05:59,901 --> 00:06:01,486
How much for everything?

128
00:06:01,486 --> 00:06:02,945
[CASHIER] 865 pesos.

129
00:06:02,945 --> 00:06:03,738
Sorry?

130
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:05,323
865 pesos!

131
00:06:05,364 --> 00:06:06,657
865 pesos?

132
00:06:08,451 --> 00:06:09,994
Jesus.

133
00:06:10,578 --> 00:06:12,747
That’s almost a thousand.

134
00:06:12,789 --> 00:06:14,290
Well, you ordered a lot!

135
00:06:14,290 --> 00:06:15,708
Fine, sorry.

136
00:06:15,708 --> 00:06:17,710
I’m just hungry. Here.

137
00:06:18,795 --> 00:06:20,505
Nothing comes cheap anymore, huh?

138
00:06:20,546 --> 00:06:22,924
Even love is expensive.

139
00:06:23,466 --> 00:06:25,218
You'll really end up cursing.

140
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:33,309
[JAO AND TANTAN LAUGH]

141
00:06:34,352 --> 00:06:36,020
You know,

142
00:06:36,521 --> 00:06:38,064
I haven’t laughed like this in a long time.

143
00:06:38,106 --> 00:06:39,857
You’re the first to make me laugh.

144
00:06:39,857 --> 00:06:41,776
Must have hit home.

145
00:06:41,776 --> 00:06:43,528
Did you and your girlfriend get into a fight?

146
00:06:43,569 --> 00:06:44,862
Is that why you've been drinking?

147
00:06:48,116 --> 00:06:49,158
What’s your name?

148
00:06:49,325 --> 00:06:50,493
Jonathan, sir.

149
00:06:51,077 --> 00:06:51,994
Just call me Tantan.

150
00:06:52,286 --> 00:06:53,412
I’m Jao.

151
00:06:53,412 --> 00:06:55,414
But I like how you call me. Sir Handsome?

152
00:06:55,456 --> 00:06:57,041
- Sir Handsome. - I like that.

153
00:06:58,084 --> 00:07:01,420
From now on, we’re best friends.

154
00:07:03,714 --> 00:07:05,842
You’re just drunk, Sir Handsome!

155
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:07,844
Let’s eat.

156
00:07:21,816 --> 00:07:22,859
Looking good!

157
00:07:35,037 --> 00:07:36,664
Very good nice!

158
00:07:52,221 --> 00:07:54,182
[SIARGAONON] Good morning!

159
00:07:55,057 --> 00:07:56,100
Good morning!

160
00:07:56,726 --> 00:07:59,145
Did you enjoy the foam party last night?

161
00:07:59,145 --> 00:08:00,980
Later, there’s another party-

162
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:03,941
Sorry, Mr. Han Bin.

163
00:08:04,525 --> 00:08:08,029
I didn’t come to Siargao to party, actually.

164
00:08:08,279 --> 00:08:09,280
I need your help.

165
00:08:09,697 --> 00:08:11,115
Yeah, sure! What is it?

166
00:08:11,532 --> 00:08:14,660
I need you to hire the best tour guide in General Luna.

167
00:08:15,411 --> 00:08:16,162
Very good!

168
00:08:16,245 --> 00:08:18,706
So, do you want a land tour or island tour?

169
00:08:19,081 --> 00:08:22,376
Land, island, north, east, west, south-

170
00:08:22,418 --> 00:08:23,127
all of it!

171
00:08:24,003 --> 00:08:25,379
Very good nice.

172
00:08:26,255 --> 00:08:27,506
You know, you’re lucky

173
00:08:27,548 --> 00:08:29,550
because we have the best tour guide

174
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:31,719
- in the entire Siargao! - Great.

175
00:08:32,094 --> 00:08:33,054
So...

176
00:08:33,971 --> 00:08:35,348
book me a tour for two days.

177
00:08:35,389 --> 00:08:36,974
Game! I will call her later.

178
00:08:36,974 --> 00:08:38,809
So, what time do you want to start tomorrow?

179
00:08:38,851 --> 00:08:40,394
No, not tomorrow.

180
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:41,812
Today.

181
00:08:42,230 --> 00:08:44,482
Today is not possible.

182
00:08:44,524 --> 00:08:46,067
She’s off duty today.

183
00:08:47,443 --> 00:08:49,278
Mr. Han Bin, you don’t understand.

184
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:53,241
I’m willing to pay a good amount

185
00:08:53,241 --> 00:08:55,034
of money for this tour.

186
00:08:56,994 --> 00:08:58,788
Because I’m looking for someone.

187
00:08:59,330 --> 00:09:01,082
Someone very important to me.

188
00:09:08,965 --> 00:09:10,591
- Good morning! - Good morning, ma'am.

189
00:09:16,973 --> 00:09:19,267
Jao, she’s here!

190
00:09:19,308 --> 00:09:22,520
The best tour guide in Siargao, Kara!

191
00:09:22,562 --> 00:09:24,021
Kara, Jao.

192
00:09:24,021 --> 00:09:25,314
Kara, Jao...

193
00:09:25,314 --> 00:09:26,023
[SIARGAONON] Karajaw!

194
00:09:26,023 --> 00:09:27,984
Like the Siargaonon term for “super”!

195
00:09:28,025 --> 00:09:29,402
Wow! Wonderful! Right?

196
00:09:29,860 --> 00:09:31,737
- He’s our VIP guest? - Yeah.

197
00:09:33,281 --> 00:09:34,573
Weren’t you that drunk

198
00:09:34,615 --> 00:09:36,575
looking for some girl last night?

199
00:09:36,617 --> 00:09:38,911
I wasn’t drunk.

200
00:09:38,911 --> 00:09:40,997
I was just tipsy. And...

201
00:09:41,247 --> 00:09:42,790
I was not looking for "some girl".

202
00:09:43,958 --> 00:09:44,834
I’m looking for Allie.

203
00:09:44,875 --> 00:09:47,461
She’s my longtime girlfriend and soon-to-be fiancée.

204
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:48,921
“Soon-to-be”?

205
00:09:49,171 --> 00:09:51,173
You seem so sure she’d say yes.

206
00:09:53,801 --> 00:09:56,554
Allie and I have been together since college so,

207
00:09:57,013 --> 00:09:59,557
I think she knows I’m marrying her.

208
00:10:00,099 --> 00:10:02,977
Sorry, I don’t mean to be rude, but...

209
00:10:02,977 --> 00:10:06,147
why would she marry someone she’s clearly avoiding?

210
00:10:06,605 --> 00:10:09,692
That’s why I need your professional help.

211
00:10:10,109 --> 00:10:12,737
Aren’t you the best tour guide in General Luna?

212
00:10:13,321 --> 00:10:15,072
Please help me find Allie.

213
00:10:16,866 --> 00:10:21,203
So, is this a tour or…

214
00:10:21,537 --> 00:10:25,124
a search party for a runaway soon-to-be fiancée?

215
00:10:27,501 --> 00:10:29,170
Two things can be true.

216
00:10:32,548 --> 00:10:33,924
Sir Han Bin!

217
00:10:33,924 --> 00:10:36,093
I don’t want to do this! I don’t want drama!

218
00:10:36,135 --> 00:10:39,221
Kara, this is not a good way to treat our guest.

219
00:10:39,221 --> 00:10:40,973
We give them five star service

220
00:10:41,015 --> 00:10:44,143
so they can give us five star reviews, remember?

221
00:10:44,143 --> 00:10:46,145
Do your job. Go, go!

222
00:10:47,521 --> 00:10:49,190
So, how do we even do it?

223
00:10:49,690 --> 00:10:51,108
This is a big island.

224
00:10:51,108 --> 00:10:52,610
Do you even know where to start?

225
00:10:53,277 --> 00:10:54,278
Actually…

226
00:10:56,405 --> 00:10:59,450
My assistant sent this earlier.

227
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:01,494
Apparently, when Allie got here,

228
00:11:01,827 --> 00:11:04,038
she deleted all her social media posts.

229
00:11:04,038 --> 00:11:06,665
But she posted this recently.

230
00:11:07,958 --> 00:11:09,585
I want to go to that spot,

231
00:11:09,585 --> 00:11:11,629
to ask nearby cafés and resorts

232
00:11:11,921 --> 00:11:13,839
if they’ve seen Allie.

233
00:11:13,839 --> 00:11:15,841
I’m sure Kara knows this spot, right?

234
00:11:17,426 --> 00:11:18,427
You do?

235
00:11:18,886 --> 00:11:20,012
Little Hawaii.

236
00:11:21,430 --> 00:11:22,431
Here we go.

237
00:11:23,349 --> 00:11:24,433
Let's go?

238
00:11:26,644 --> 00:11:27,645
Go on!

239
00:11:40,408 --> 00:11:45,204
[CELLPHONE RINGING]

240
00:11:48,707 --> 00:11:50,167
Burgos is pretty far.

241
00:11:50,209 --> 00:11:51,669
You can get some sleep.

242
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:54,672
You still look hungover.

243
00:11:56,632 --> 00:11:58,008
Do I still smell like alcohol?

244
00:11:59,593 --> 00:12:01,595
Why do you even think I would know?

245
00:12:01,804 --> 00:12:04,765
Do I look like I sniff people for a hobby?

246
00:12:06,308 --> 00:12:07,726
Sorry, just asking.

247
00:12:15,568 --> 00:12:16,694
Wow.

248
00:12:18,487 --> 00:12:20,865
I love the fresh air here.

249
00:12:21,824 --> 00:12:23,701
It’s not the same in Manila.

250
00:12:26,370 --> 00:12:29,248
[JAO] How long until Burgos again?

251
00:12:29,498 --> 00:12:31,667
40 to 50 kilometers.

252
00:12:32,543 --> 00:12:35,880
It’s the northern tip of Siargao,

253
00:12:36,464 --> 00:12:38,466
overlooking the Pacific Ocean.

254
00:12:41,302 --> 00:12:42,970
To be honest with you,

255
00:12:43,179 --> 00:12:46,140
I still don’t know how we’ll find your ex-girlfriend.

256
00:12:46,932 --> 00:12:47,975
Fiancée.

257
00:12:49,101 --> 00:12:50,644
Ex-fiancée.

258
00:12:52,062 --> 00:12:54,523
Just fiancée. No “ex.”

259
00:12:54,982 --> 00:12:57,109
Okay. Let’s be positive.

260
00:12:57,860 --> 00:12:59,570
Let’s manifest that.

261
00:13:07,203 --> 00:13:08,329
Kara, stop the car.

262
00:13:08,621 --> 00:13:09,872
What, why?

263
00:13:11,290 --> 00:13:13,959
Hey, if you're planning to pee, you can't do that here, okay?

264
00:13:15,461 --> 00:13:17,087
Can you just relax? I’m not taking a leak.

265
00:13:17,087 --> 00:13:18,297
I want to buy something.

266
00:13:23,093 --> 00:13:24,428
[SIARGAONON] Good morning!

267
00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:25,679
[SIARGAONON] Good morning, sir!

268
00:13:25,721 --> 00:13:27,348
Buy some Pan de Totoy.

269
00:13:27,389 --> 00:13:28,015
Any more left?

270
00:13:28,057 --> 00:13:28,807
Of course.

271
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:30,768
[JAO] Looks delicious.

272
00:13:30,809 --> 00:13:32,603
I’ll take all of it.

273
00:13:32,645 --> 00:13:33,270
[VENDOR] Okay.

274
00:13:35,147 --> 00:13:35,814
You’re amazing.

275
00:13:35,814 --> 00:13:37,733
Do you always help your mom?

276
00:13:38,234 --> 00:13:39,151
What grade are you in?

277
00:13:39,151 --> 00:13:40,194
Grade two.

278
00:13:41,111 --> 00:13:43,989
What do you want to be when you grow up?

279
00:13:44,031 --> 00:13:46,951
A pilot. I want to ride a plane.

280
00:13:46,992 --> 00:13:49,495
You can do it. Just study hard, okay?

281
00:13:49,954 --> 00:13:51,330
[JAO] What’s your name?

282
00:13:51,330 --> 00:13:52,206
[CHILD] Abong.

283
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:54,375
[JAO] No, not Abong anymore...

284
00:13:54,416 --> 00:13:57,753
It’s Captain Abong, Pilot.

285
00:13:58,045 --> 00:13:58,879
Pilot.

286
00:13:59,255 --> 00:14:00,631
Very good nice!

287
00:14:01,215 --> 00:14:02,424
Here you go.

288
00:14:02,591 --> 00:14:04,176
- Keep the change. - Thank you!

289
00:14:04,218 --> 00:14:05,094
[SIARGAONON] Thank you!

290
00:14:05,135 --> 00:14:06,053
Take care.

291
00:14:10,516 --> 00:14:12,059
[JAO] Have you been in Siargao long?

292
00:14:13,310 --> 00:14:15,896
What makes you think I’m not from here?

293
00:14:19,316 --> 00:14:20,317
Am I wrong?

294
00:14:20,859 --> 00:14:22,236
Did you grow up here?

295
00:14:26,282 --> 00:14:28,367
I’ve been here for seven years.

296
00:14:29,910 --> 00:14:32,204
So you're originally from Manila?

297
00:14:34,665 --> 00:14:35,958
I’m from Makati.

298
00:14:38,419 --> 00:14:40,963
Allie and I started dating in college.

299
00:14:42,381 --> 00:14:46,260
We looked for jobs together in Makati after graduation.

300
00:14:47,177 --> 00:14:48,512
I started as a

301
00:14:48,554 --> 00:14:50,764
Marketing Assistant at a retail company.

302
00:14:50,806 --> 00:14:53,809
Then Allie became a Visual Merchandiser.

303
00:14:55,311 --> 00:14:59,189
We’ve been living together for five years now.

304
00:15:01,108 --> 00:15:02,610
I thought we were doing okay.

305
00:15:05,029 --> 00:15:06,071
Then one day,

306
00:15:06,322 --> 00:15:07,906
she said she wanted to go on a solo trip

307
00:15:07,906 --> 00:15:09,617
here in Siargao for a week.

308
00:15:10,743 --> 00:15:12,786
She said she needed a break.

309
00:15:13,537 --> 00:15:19,084
Her workload got a lot heavier after she got promoted to Strategic Planner.

310
00:15:19,084 --> 00:15:20,336
Meanwhile,

311
00:15:21,545 --> 00:15:25,174
I ventured out, looked for other options, and then right now,

312
00:15:25,507 --> 00:15:28,344
I’m the Project Development Head for a real estate company.

313
00:15:28,510 --> 00:15:30,471
You don’t need to tell me this.

314
00:15:32,222 --> 00:15:33,724
Kara, I need to.

315
00:15:33,724 --> 00:15:35,601
So you can understand why I'm doing this.

316
00:15:37,936 --> 00:15:40,731
First three days,

317
00:15:40,731 --> 00:15:42,483
she still kept in touch.

318
00:15:42,524 --> 00:15:45,402
Sending photos, videos, places she visited,

319
00:15:45,402 --> 00:15:47,613
video calls, text messages.

320
00:15:48,656 --> 00:15:50,324
Then on the fifth day,

321
00:15:51,659 --> 00:15:54,453
she suddenly messaged that she won't be coming home.

322
00:15:57,206 --> 00:15:59,166
You really don’t have to share this with me.

323
00:15:59,208 --> 00:16:00,542
I thought she was joking.

324
00:16:02,753 --> 00:16:04,004
I thought it was just a prank.

325
00:16:04,046 --> 00:16:07,383
And then, on the day she was supposed to arrive in Manila,

326
00:16:08,884 --> 00:16:10,469
I waited at the airport.

327
00:16:12,012 --> 00:16:14,223
But she never showed up.

328
00:16:14,264 --> 00:16:15,432
Seriously.

329
00:16:16,642 --> 00:16:18,894
I don’t need to know all these things.

330
00:16:20,270 --> 00:16:21,522
Stop dumping it on me!

331
00:16:21,563 --> 00:16:24,983
I'm just your tour guide helping you find your ex-girlfriend.

332
00:16:25,150 --> 00:16:26,443
I'm not your therapist.

333
00:16:51,802 --> 00:16:53,053
Siargao!

334
00:16:54,722 --> 00:16:57,057
Please bring Allie back to me!

335
00:17:06,442 --> 00:17:07,651
Please, Allie.

336
00:17:10,362 --> 00:17:11,530
Come back.

337
00:17:14,491 --> 00:17:15,492
Please.

338
00:17:52,613 --> 00:17:53,614
Please.

339
00:17:57,701 --> 00:17:59,787
Help me find Allie.

340
00:18:05,083 --> 00:18:08,170
I’ll search all of Siargao if I have to.

341
00:18:12,925 --> 00:18:13,926
You know,

342
00:18:15,803 --> 00:18:18,472
it’s hard to find someone who doesn’t want to be found.

343
00:18:20,724 --> 00:18:21,934
But, sure.

344
00:18:24,228 --> 00:18:25,687
I’ll help you.

345
00:18:27,981 --> 00:18:29,817
So you can get closure.

346
00:18:34,947 --> 00:18:35,989
Thanks.

347
00:19:04,351 --> 00:19:06,353
[RINGING]

348
00:19:06,478 --> 00:19:11,275
[CELLPHONE RINGING]

349
00:19:12,484 --> 00:19:13,235
Kara?

350
00:19:13,443 --> 00:19:14,319
[KARA] Allie?

351
00:19:15,612 --> 00:19:18,240
He’s here. He’s with me.

352
00:19:36,842 --> 00:19:38,802
Sorry about what I said earlier.

353
00:19:38,844 --> 00:19:41,430
I'll leave a bad review for you and Katig.

354
00:19:41,847 --> 00:19:43,056
[JAO LAUGHS]

355
00:19:43,557 --> 00:19:44,433
Just kidding!

356
00:19:44,433 --> 00:19:46,393
You showed zero empathy.

357
00:19:46,435 --> 00:19:48,020
I just told you a really dramatic story.

358
00:19:48,020 --> 00:19:49,062
But that was all real.

359
00:19:49,104 --> 00:19:50,689
Carol, this is Jao.

360
00:19:50,731 --> 00:19:52,065
Jao, Carol.

361
00:19:52,107 --> 00:19:54,109
She owns Carol’s Inn.

362
00:19:54,651 --> 00:19:55,986
Do you eat kinilaw (Filipino ceviche)?

363
00:19:56,028 --> 00:19:57,821
- I'm great… at making kinilaw. - Of course.

364
00:19:58,488 --> 00:20:01,867
[JAO] Actually, I made a list of all the places Allie could go.

365
00:20:01,909 --> 00:20:03,368
I don’t think she’ll come here.

366
00:20:03,410 --> 00:20:05,329
Maybe you recognize her.

367
00:20:05,746 --> 00:20:06,955
Next stop?

368
00:20:10,042 --> 00:20:11,084
Kara!

369
00:20:18,258 --> 00:20:19,259
Allie?
